{"parse":{"title":"The Golden Stairs","pageid":38054331,"revid":812636671,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the painting by Edward Burne-Jones. For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/Golden_Stairs_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Golden Stairs (disambiguation)\">Golden Stairs</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:right;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">The Golden Stairs</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Edward Burne-Jones The Golden Stairs.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg/275px-Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" width=\"275\" height=\"650\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg/413px-Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg/550px-Edward_Burne-Jones_The_Golden_Stairs.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1287\" data-file-height=\"3040\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Edward_Burne-Jones\" title=\"Edward Burne-Jones\">Edward Burne-Jones</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\n1880</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Medium</th><td class=\"category\">\nOil on panel</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\n269.2&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;116.8&#160;cm&#32;(106.0&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;46.0&#160;in)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\nTate Britain, London</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Golden Stairs</b></i> is one of the best-known paintings by the <a href=\"/wiki/Pre-Raphaelite_Brotherhood\" title=\"Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood\">Pre-Raphaelite</a> artist <a href=\"/wiki/Edward_Burne-Jones\" title=\"Edward Burne-Jones\">Edward Burne-Jones</a>.  It was begun in 1876 and exhibited at the <a href=\"/wiki/Grosvenor_Gallery\" title=\"Grosvenor Gallery\">Grosvenor Gallery</a> in 1880.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Wood_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wood-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Unlike many of Burne-Jones's works, <i>The Golden Stairs</i> is not based on a literary source. It has been called <a href=\"/wiki/Symbolism_(arts)\" title=\"Symbolism (arts)\">Symbolist</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> as it has no recognisable narrative, but rather sets a mood.  It is a harmony of color in the tradition of the <a href=\"/wiki/Aestheticism\" title=\"Aestheticism\">Aesthetic</a> works of the 1860s and 1870s, as a group of young women carrying musical instruments descend a spiraling staircase, dressed in classically inspired robes in tones of white, shading to gold and silver.<sup id=\"cite_ref-smarth_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-smarth-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman247_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman247-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Critic <a href=\"/wiki/F._G._Stephens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"F. G. Stephens\">F. G. Stephens</a> wrote in <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Athenaeum_(British_magazine)\" title=\"The Athenaeum (British magazine)\">The Athenaeum</a></i> that the musicians \"troop past like spirits in an enchanted dream ... whither they go, who they are, there is nothing to tell\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><i>The Golden Stairs</i> was one of many paintings Burne-Jones sketched out in 1872 following a trip to Italy.  He began work on the canvas in 1876 and finished it in great haste in April 1880, just days before the Grosvenor Gallery exhibition was to open.  Stephens found in the painting echoes of the work of <a href=\"/wiki/Piero_della_Francesca\" title=\"Piero della Francesca\">Piero della Francesca</a>, whose frescoes Burne-Jones had seen and copied in 1871.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman247_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman247-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The figures of the musicians were drawn from professional models, but the heads are young women of Burne-Jones's circle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Some identifications have been made as follows.\n</p><p>His daughter Margaret is fourth from top, holding a trumpet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MacCarthy102_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MacCarthy102-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Edith Gellibrand, known by the stage name Edith Chester, is seventh from top, seen stooping.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/May_Morris\" title=\"May Morris\">May Morris</a>, daughter of <a href=\"/wiki/William_Morris\" title=\"William Morris\">William Morris</a>, is ninth from top, holding a violin. Frances Graham, later known as Lady Horner, daughter of <a href=\"/wiki/William_Graham_(Glasgow_MP)\" title=\"William Graham (Glasgow MP)\">William Graham</a>, is bottom left, holding cymbals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MacCarthy102_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MacCarthy102-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Standing behind her on the stairs is <a href=\"/wiki/Mary_Gladstone\" title=\"Mary Gladstone\">Mary Gladstone</a>, daughter of <a href=\"/wiki/William_Gladstone\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"William Gladstone\">William Gladstone</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Others include Laura Tennant, later known as <a href=\"/wiki/Laura_Lyttelton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Laura Lyttelton\">Laura Lyttelton</a>, and Mary Stuart-Wortley, later <a href=\"/wiki/Ralph_King-Milbanke,_2nd_Earl_of_Lovelace\" title=\"Ralph King-Milbanke, 2nd Earl of Lovelace\">Lady Lovelace</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The painting was purchased by <a href=\"/wiki/Cyril_Flower,_1st_Baron_Battersea\" title=\"Cyril Flower, 1st Baron Battersea\">Cyril Flower</a> (1843\u20131907), later Lord Battersea, a politician and art patron, and was bequeathed by him to the <a href=\"/wiki/Tate_Britain\" title=\"Tate Britain\">Tate Gallery</a>, where it remains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wildman_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wildman-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Wood_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wood-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Studies\">Studies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Golden_Stairs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Studies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg/101px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg\" width=\"101\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg/151px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg/202px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_the_Head_of_a_Girl_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpeg 2x\" data-file-width=\"420\" data-file-height=\"500\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Study of the head of a girl, 1879\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/90px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/135px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/179px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_of_two_girls_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"449\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Study of two girls\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/87px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg\" width=\"87\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/130px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg/173px-Edward_Burne-Jones_Study_for_the_Golden_Stairs.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"405\" data-file-height=\"560\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Study of a musician\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Golden_Stairs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Golden_Stairs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em;width: 210px; float: right; clear: right; margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em\"><caption>External video</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;text-align: left\">\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"128\" data-file-height=\"128\" /> <a rel=\"nofo